cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "H20 LLM Inference Cookbook: Tuned Triton Fused-MoE Configs for NVIDIA H20"
message: >-
  If you use the configs, benchmarks, or methodology from this repository in
  your research, deployment, or downstream tuning, please cite it as below.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Yichuan
    family-names: Shi
    alias: CarrotSwordsman
    email: mershi@tencent.com
repository-code: "https://github.com/CarrotSwordsman/H20-LLM-Cookbook"
url: "https://github.com/CarrotSwordsman/H20-LLM-Cookbook"
abstract: >-
  A reproducible benchmark suite and tuning recipe collection for NVIDIA H20
  LLM inference, focused on the Triton fused MoE kernel path used by vLLM and
  SGLang. Ships 24 tuned configurations (12 bf16 + 12 fp8_w8a8 per-tensor)
  covering Mixtral 8x7B, Qwen MoE, and DeepSeek-V2-Lite shapes, along with
  standalone tuning scripts and a 36-point default-vs-tuned benchmark table.
  Geomean speedup 1.09x, peak 1.74x over vLLM's default-fallback heuristic.
keywords:
  - vllm
  - sglang
  - triton
  - fused-moe
  - mixture-of-experts
  - nvidia-h20
  - llm-inference
  - kernel-tuning
  - benchmark
license: MIT
